Neotoma Sites on Tribal, Public, and Protected Land

2024-03-18

This is a brief survey of Neotoma sites on tribal lands, federal lands, and protected lands. These surveys were done using shapefiles from the following sources: 1. Federal census TIGER 2019 2. ArcGIS hub dataset of federal lands, and 3. The Florida Natural Areas Inventory.

There are 691 distinct Neotoma sites (out of roughly 22500) on federally recognized reservation lands.

There are no Neotoma sites on federally recognized reservation land in Florida.

There are 2421 Neotoma sites (out of roughly 22500) on federal land.

In Florida, there are 129 Neotoma sites on federal land.

There are 235 Neotoma sites on protected land in Florida, according to the Florida Natural Areas Inventory.The map shows sites that are locally protected (L), privately protected (P), or state protected (S). Sites on federally protected land (F) or under joint jurisdiction can be seen in the above table.
